HEADWORD: Weazen
<hw>Wea"zen</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Wizen</er>.]</ety> <def>Thin; sharp; withered; wizened; <as>as, a
<ex>weazen</ex> face</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They were <qex>weazen</qex> and shriveled.</q>
<rj><qau>Dickens.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Weazeny</ent>⟦br⟧
